--- body ---
## Problem

`BUDGET_HOUSEKEEPING = 0.75` and `BUDGET_PICK_TICKET = 0.75` are global constants
in beat.py. Small projects (aedist: $0.37 per run) pay the same ceiling as large
ones (Climate_finance: $0.51+). Raising the global to cover large projects wastes
headroom on small ones.

## Solution

Add per-project budget overrides to `beat-settings.json` (or a per-project
`.claude/beat-project.json`):

```json
{
  "projects": {
    "Climate_finance": { "budget_housekeeping": 0.75, "budget_pick_ticket": 0.75 },
    "fuzzy-corpus":    { "budget_housekeeping": 0.75, "budget_pick_ticket": 0.50 },
    "aedist-technical-report": { "budget_housekeeping": 0.40 }
  }
}
```

beat.py reads the override for the current project at startup, falls back to global.

## Acceptance criteria

- beat.py reads per-project budget overrides
- aedist-technical-report and cadens run with lower budgets than Climate_finance
- Defaults unchanged if no override present
